        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 900 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Camden, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dallas Lake, Belknap, Dannelly Reservoir, Collirene, Tilden,
Carlowville, Minter, Farmersville, and Fostoria.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
south central Alabama.</instruction>
